The paper deals with the compression of a Gaussian source sequence in a communication network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The presence of an eavesdropper also suggests the possibility of cryptographic techniques, placing the paper in the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of game theory in the analysis of the communication network may also suggest the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of information theoretic regions, which may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
